		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.65]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Slipskin&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Who said bards are not any good at soloing?&nbsp;&nbsp;They're have never played a bard (at least not to any reasonable level). Bards can kite as good as any druid or wizard.  It just requires busier finger work on the keyboard.  <br><br>Bards get track skill at level 35. Not as good as a ranger but good enough for most folks needs.<br><br>When grouped, bards have a different job than rangers.  The bard's job is to fill in for whatever else is missing or to enhance the existing capabilities of the group.  Missing an enchanter? Get a bard. Missing a secondary tank? Get a bard.  Can't afford the extortion folks are charging for KEI? Get a bard.  Missing a shaman? Get a bard.  Bards are like that BASF Corporation.  We don't make the group - we make the group better.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target="akztarg">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
