		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.77]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Althas&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Completely agree with Slipskin on this one. I have had a limited experiecne of ALL classes (highest being Ranger 38 and my new Bard 51) and for me Bards solo as good as or better than ANY class. Just a shame I didnt disvover this till just recently after being put off by these guides tht say Bards arnt to good. Believe me they are COMPLETELY wrong.<br><br>AFter leaving Paludal Caverns at 26 all the way to lvl 51 I think I have gained about half a level from groping, all the rest has been solo.&nbsp;&nbsp;BUT dont think they are like Necros, and really only suited to solo, they are not. they are just as good in a group, this was my own preference for playing.<br><br>Bards are a support class, NOT out and out Melee, so if you are looking for Melee then Ranger or Monk would be better.  Bards are not a Spotlight class, like a Tank, Cleric, Wizard e.t.c.  Most groups wont realise just how much we do, until they have grouped with a Bard who knows his stuff, then wonder why things go a lot slower after we gone. No Enchanter, the Bard can Mez and mana regen (whith the later being the only thing people think a Bard can do.) No Shaman? Bard slow, Bard haste. No Druid, Bard damage shield. To much agro, Bard charm a mob to help out.  Apart from Root, I dont think there is a role a Bard cant slip into t a moments notice.<br><br>As we are Jacks of all trades, we are Master of them all. Yes the specialized classes will beat us on their little thing, but ask a warrior to anything much more than tank and they are stuck.<br><br>If you want a hectic, varied, non-stop, but somewhat unappreciated life in EQ. then Bards are the best. Such versitility, but under appreciated by all.<br><br>The power of Bards to me was summed up from my time in Oasis of Marr when I was playing with the spectres.  There was a lvl 48 Paladin sat there plodding away with 1 spectre, rest, med some mana then do 1 more. I asked if she minded if I shared the island with her (I was lvl 40 by the way) which she agreed to.  So I pull the rest of the Spectres (6 or 7) to a nearby beach and started to Swarm Kite them.  She panics at seeing this and runs to my aid, of which I can do nothing but respect her for that.  She gets agro off them and runs to SRO zone line.  I stop and sit waiting for them to come back, sent her a tell appologising for not telling here I was fine and ment to pull them all.  And she basically faints at this and could believe me, so she cameand sat and watched me do all of them in about 4 or 5 mins without taking a single hit.  At this all she said was WOW.<br><br>Now that is not just me, that is the power of a Bard and the ability of what you can do.<br><br>And Slipskin I love that last Line.  Bards dont make the group, We make the group better ;-)  Summs it up in a few words.<br><br>My only little bit of advice is DO NOT TWINK the Bard when you start. PLay as a complete new character as you really need to learn the class in this environment fully to play it well. You need to learn what all your songs do, when to sing them,when not to, combinations of twists for certain situations, what to do in an emergency to save everyone and yourself e.t.c.  and being twinked you will never learn this, so you will be another bad bard on the streets, instead of owning them.  Get better gear once you hit 25ish and have a handle on how to play properly.<br><br>Ok sorry for rambling on for way to long, once I et started I can never stop.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sun May 11 02:59:59 2003</em></p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table b